<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920311-0041</DOCNO><DOCID>920311-0041.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Marsh andamp; McLennan Cos.:   European Offices Realigned,   Including New Acquisitions</HL><DATE>03/11/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C9</SO><CO>   MMC WNEWS</CO><MS>FINANCIAL (FIN)</MS><IN>DIVERSIFIED FINANCIAL SERVICES (FIS)</IN><NS>PERSONNEL ANNOUNCEMENTS (PER)</NS><RE>EUROPE (EU)NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Insurance broker Marsh andamp; McLennan Inc. said it organizedits European operations under a new Marsh andamp; McLennan Europeentity.   The unit, operating in 16 countries, has 100 offices withmore than 6,500 employees. It reflects existing operations aswell as recently acquired businesses. Previously, Marsh andamp;McLennan had a Continental organization and a separate U.K.unit.</LP><TEXT>   Roland Seul, managing director in Munich, was namedchairman of Marsh andamp; McLennan Europe. The unit's boardincludes about a dozen senior operating officers from thevarious countries.   Marsh andamp; McLennan Europe reports to David D. Holbrook,president of Marsh andamp; McLennan Inc., a major subsidiary ofMarsh andamp; McLennan Cos., of New York. He said the new unit&quot;recognizes how clients are going to be operating in theEuropean Community.&quot; With recent acquisitions, he added, &quot;weare positioned exactly where we wanted to be.&quot;</TEXT></DOC>